               <msContents>
                  <summary>Chants called Zimmare for the whole year, 20th c, with musical notation. with very nice cloth book cover that envelops foredge and spine, etc. F. iv r: The chant of Christmas, with musical notation, written in blue ink.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                    <locus from="1r" to="37v" facs="005">Fols 1r–37v</locus>
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2610Zemmar">Zǝmmāre</title>
                    <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                    <note>Chants for the whole year. Includes musical notation</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                    <locus from="38r" to="116r" facs="042">Fols 38r–116r</locus>
                  <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1990Mawase">Mawāśǝʾǝt</title>
                  <note>Includes musical notation</note>
                  </msItem>
                  </msContents>
